info.description:
pylineprof
==========

Python line profiler.

usage
-----

::

    $ python3 example.py
    example.py
                            | import time
                            | import pylineprof
                            | 
                            | 
                            | def slowfib(n):
         0.001ms          1 |     a, b = 0, 1
         0.329ms         11 |     for i in range(n):
         0.115ms         10 |         a, b = b, a + b
      5030.598ms         10 |         time.sleep(.5)
         0.017ms          1 |     return a
                            | 
                            | 
                            | if __name__ == '__main__':
                            |     profiler = pylineprof.LineProfiler()
                            | 
                            |     with profiler:
      5040.386ms          1 |         slowfib(10)
                            | 
                            |     profiler.report()

alternatives
------------

* `line_profiler <https://github.com/rkern/line_profiler>`_
* `pprofile <https://github.com/vpelletier/pprofile>`_: pure-python version
